  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Coloscopy may be a painful procedure for the patient. This is due to a loop-formation of the
      coloscope. A 3D-real time imager produced by Olympus creates a real-time image of the scope
      while a traditional fluoroscopy device will only show instant pictures. We want to
      investigate whether the 3D-imager causes the patient less pain and is more time consuming
      than ordinary fluoroscopy
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Results published in Holme et.al. Gastrointestinal Endoscopy 2011;73:1215-1222.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
